VSTM SCRIP TRACKING IS CRITICALOkay follow me on this if the 16 scrips reported 2 weeks ago reflected refills from scrips that were new a month before that then approx one month from the 16 scrip week we should see a week with those 16 scrips refilled again plus any new scrips Logically the 5th week from the 16 scrip week we should see 20 or more scrips If so were on track for steady growth If NOT then the refills are not repeating or accumulating Its not rocket science Either scrips and refills are growing and accumulatingor not Patients stay on Copiktra 2 years or more but some stop due to adverse effects If they are staying on the drugs refills will repeat and INCREASE every 4 or 5 weeks and this should show up in scrip reports
